      "outputs_written": {
        "prose": "A solitary figure stands in a cramped, industrial laundry room filled with steam and hanging white linens. The scene is rendered in the style of Yoshitomo Nara. A young woman with oversized, pale skin and a wide, unsmiling mouth wears a loose, oversized denim jumpsuit. Her hair is a mass of black, slightly unruly strands that frame a round, expressive face. She holds a heavy, wet towel in one hand while leaning against a rusted metal pipe. The lighting is flat and diffused, coming from a single high window that casts soft, elongated shadows against the peeling paint of the walls. The floor is slick with condensation, reflecting the muted colors of the room. Nara's characteristic use of thick, dark outlines defines every curve of her body and the folds of her fabric. The air feels thick with humidity, and the colors are a mix of pastel pinks and deep indigos that contrast with the stark, monochromatic background.",
